the cyclical nature of the month of the year to the network and to enforce the network to encode the annual cycle of precipitation over the study area (see, Liu et al., 2018; Scheuerer et al., 2017).
We retain the average value of continuous ranked probability score (CRPS) of predictive CSGDs as the loss function for training the weights and biases of the ANN-CSGD. The ANN is trained by minimizing the CRPS computed using collocated and coincidental forecast-observation pairs over training data (see the Appendix B for the mathematical deÔ¨Ånition of CRPS)

